CAPE TOWN - Police are investigating after a taxi crashed near Parliament on Friday morning, injuring 13 people, including 12 children. The vehicle was transporting 22 children to school when it smashed into a bollard outside the parliamentary precinct. The police's Andre Traut: "The driver and 12 schoolchildren were injured and were admitted to hospital for treatment. A case of reckless and or negligent driving has been registered." Download the Eyewitness News app to your iOS  or Android  device.